Product Information: The ASUS Transformer Book T100 (T100TA-C1-GR) is a great choice if you want a light, snappy tablet but also want to retain the option of using a physical keyboard. The Transformer Book T100 is a true 2-in-1 type device. It has a 10.1 tablet-like form factor, but also has a dedicated dock for an equally-sized keyboard attachment. The keyboard slots in at the bottom of the tablet part; once connected, it can fold up or stand just like typical netbooks or laptops. Work on your personal or business content with the Transformer Book in notebook mode, or detach the tablet module to show movies or other media to your friends quickly and easily. The Transformer Book has all the power of a tablet in a more versatile product. The ASUS Transformer Book T100 runs the Windows operating system in a way that is optimized for tablets. It has the Windows touchscreen keyboard but also works seamlessly with the Transformer Book’s keyboard dock whenever it is in place. The ASUS Transformer Book T100 has an Intel Atom z3740 quad-core processor clocked at 1.46GHz and 2GB of RAM. This should handle any music, movies or files you want the T100 to run. It can also turbo-boost to as much as 2.39 GHz, depending on the load required of the system. The Intel Atom z3740 CPU also comes with Intel integrated HD graphics to enhance this experience. The display that shows them is a 1366x768p (HD) IPS panel, which benefits brightness, clarity and viewing angles on the Transformer Book T100. You can also store documents, music and other files on the T100’s 64GB of built-in storage. This laptop is also built for productivity. It comes with Windows 8.1 out of the box, which supports apps such as Microsoft Office and OneNote. You can type full documents on the ASUS Transformer Book T100, which can then be stored on the 2-in-1’s 64GB internal memory. Alternatively, you can back these files up using a USB drive. The ASUS Transformer Book T100 has a full-sized USB 3.0 port. It also features a Micro USB port, which may be useful in transferring files to or from a PC. The ASUS Transformer Book T100 also has a Mini HDMI port, to transfer its screen’s contents to an external monitor. It also has dual speakers and an audio jack for enhanced audio quality and enjoyment. This is all powered by a 31W/HR battery, which is rated to last for up to 11 hours a day. The ASUS Transformer Book T100 is a truly versatile 2-in-1 device. Combine the tablet and its keyboard dock for an ultrabook experience, or take the tablet alone for some portable, convenient media consumption on a 10-inch screen. With the T100 in notebook mode, you can mix and match between using the capacitive touchscreen, physical keys, and integrated trackpad. This is all brought together by Windows for mobile computing. The ASUS Transformer Book T100 is a great all-around note-taking, media-playing, and mobile computing companion.
